AIM:
   To search for a given element (key) in an array by checking each element sequentially from the beginning to the end and return its position if found, otherwise indicate that the element is not present.
ALGORITHM :
    Input: Array A of size n, element key to search
Output: Index of key if found, otherwise -1


Start


Set i = 0


Repeat while i < n:
a. If A[i] == key, return i
b. Else increment i


If the loop ends, return -1 (key not found)


Stop


Time Complexity:


Best case: O(1)


Worst case: O(n)


Average case: O(n)



ðŸ’» PROGRAM (C Language)
#include <stdio.h>

int linearSearch(int arr[], int n, int key) {
    for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
        if (arr[i] == key)
            return i;   // element found
    }
    return -1; // not found
}

int main() {
    int n, key;

    printf("Enter size of array: ");
    scanf("%d", &n);

    int arr[n];
    printf("Enter %d elements:\n", n);
    for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
        scanf("%d", &arr[i]);
    }

    printf("Enter element to search: ");
    scanf("%d", &key);

    int result = linearSearch(arr, n, key);

    if (result == -1)
        printf("Element not found.\n");
    else
        printf("Element found at index %d.\n", result);

    return 0;
}
